{
  "stem": "18581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 329.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I had to prepare myself and I had the exams.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I pass the exams.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, of course, I studied in Lithuanian high school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the same time, I continued to have Hebrew Bible and Talmud classes every day, by a special teacher that my father imported from [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the [INAUDIBLE], the-- my rabbi was called Rabbi [NON-ENGLISH] [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH] [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And like in the Bible, I was Yehoshua.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was the pupil, the disciple of Moses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- and he was very proud of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was his first student.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, other people-- after my father brought this teacher from another town-- I mean, let him-- they also enjoyed studying with the same teacher.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Literature.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Literature.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had-- I was very lucky to have, in the state high school, a very bright teacher.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was actually a former pilot at the Lithuanian Air Force.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But because of problem-- vision problems, he had to use glasses-- at that time, they wouldn't have pilots with glasses.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he went to Grenoble in France for a second degree, for a-- in-- in literature.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when he came back, he was a teacher of Lithuanian language and-- and literature.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And literature meant [INAUDIBLE] literature.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So at the beginning of every year, he used to give us a list of 65 or 70 books that we had to read during the year.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were examined on this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, he used to take, let's say, from the French literature, Moliere, from English literature, Shakespeare; from the German literature, of course, Goethe, Schiller, Heine, [NON-ENGLISH], Uhland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we got a very well-rounded-- also from the Polish literature, [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], or [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- and of course, from the Russian literature, that was Gogol and Dostoyevsky.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
